TY  - JOUR
T1  - Investment, Scale, and Growth
AU  - Barzel, Yoram
Y1  - 1971/03/01
PY  - 1971
DA  - 1971/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/259740
DO  - 10.1086/259740
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 214
EP  - 231
VL  - 79
IS  - 2
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - There are many economic activities where the cost function can be approximated by a fixed initial cost and a constant (sometimes zero) marginal cost as with book publishing, public utilities, and innovations. In the absence of technical advance, an economy that grows in scale could nevertheless exhibit growth in per capita income by taking advantage of the economies of scale afforded. To the extent, however, that these production processes are in the public domain, overinvestment, manifested either in premature entry or in duplication of resources, will occur, and the growth potential, to a large extent, will be lost.
AB  - There are many economic activities where the cost function can be approximated by a fixed initial cost and a constant (sometimes zero) marginal cost as with book publishing, public utilities, and innovations. In the absence of technical advance, an economy that grows in scale could nevertheless exhibit growth in per capita income by taking advantage of the economies of scale afforded. To the extent, however, that these production processes are in the public domain, overinvestment, manifested either in premature entry or in duplication of resources, will occur, and the growth potential, to a large extent, will be lost.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/259740
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/259740
Y2  - 2024/03/22
